    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_477023">Wasn't really sure what to call this thread but I wanted to start a conversation on the evolving state of the rogue class with the addition of new poisons. I've been playing since release and only raid on occasion and have played every class through at least lvl 80- and have foolishly deleted a lot of vet-aa enabled alts due to situational boredom.  I have always preferred the group game to raiding. Just mentionning these things as a preface for my statements and bias.<br />
Ok- a few things.<br />
1. If rogue dps balance is partially being addressed through poisons then the droprate for jolt poisen ingredients needs to increase.  Even after the upcoming changes to poison aggro. <br />
2. Droprate for all/all poisons also needs to jump to allow other classes the ability to scale dps upward in line with rogues- and to create a viable but not excessively priced marketplace for them at all levels.<br />
3. The 2 poisons at a time rule is Genious! It allows for help to control aggro in groups and allows for a bump up in rogue ability to solo.  Mercs helped rogues solo, but without anywhere near the efficiency of other melée classes. Utility poisons help with this and cut downtime a bit. Comparitively- in the solo realm- all classes trump rogues. Most melée will gather aa at 3x rogue rates in levels 65 to 80- I cannot speak accurately beyond that. And since sizable aa counts are needed for operational viability at higher levels- this is a sizable handicap when many farm aa solo. Utility poisons have helped, but the gap is huge still. I propose strengthening or broadening these utility potions to narrow or elimate this gap. <br />
4. If 2 poisens is genious, more is brilliant! Allow for up to 4 poisons through aa- raiders won't use 4 buffslots for them but solo-group might. 1 damage proc, 2 debuff type and either a general utility type or let damage potions vs different resists stack and only one procs- mebby highlight the buff to denote active poison. As I write, that doesn't seem like such a good idea- but more poison specific aa certainly does- make whole new lines of aa- esp since rogues have fewer aa lines than most.<br />
5. Thank you for starting to make rogues more enjoyable- it's working.</div>
