</div>I'd like to second this idea, with Jolt, Slow and Snare poisons being rotated on a regular basis.  I'd say Jolt poisons would be the most useful for most raiders and groupers, with slow and snare being the most likely choices for soloing.<br />
<br />
In fact, a combo poison that does a little bit of snare and a decent chunk of slow would be perhaps one of the best soloing poisons around.  In other words, something a bit like the old Stiffening Ergot poison effect, but with a lesser snare effect than a pure snaring poison and a lesser slow effect than a pure slowing poison would be really nice.  Make this one a &quot;quest only&quot;, no-trade poison with the usual one week lock out on the task if you feel the need to control the amount of it available in the world, especially if it is on a rotation with some of the other poisons.<br />
<br />
Or hey, how about giving us a choice of rewards the way some tasks do?  Rogues could pick the poison they need most.<br />
<br />
Just a thought.</div>
