    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_478055">Rotation would be ok, but i think a better option would be what they currently do with almost every task that has more than one reward option.  Like they did with the Annivesary god tasks, let you select the potion(poison) type you desire, and it gives you the level appropriate components of that selection.<br />
<br />
The could make them no trade, but then they would have to make a seperate no trade version of every new component, which didnt work so well with them doing just a handful of new spells for an exploitable quest..<br />
<br />
Or they could leave them as the tradeable versions, which would add a decent amount of components into the 'tradepool'.  Tradeskillers doing the tasks could easily get a stack of the ingrediants they require, and the non-tradesmen can bring the baz prices down due to more supply.</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
