    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_478116">What I'm finding is that when I'm using the level 85 Bite of the Shissar for dps and the level 40 Quellious for jolt, I'm good as long as the tank in the group is using the level 40 Scorpions poison for extra agro.   So far, all of this is vendor purchasable.<br />
<br />
We don't necessarily need more drops for our jolt, more gormar drops for the agro potion for tanks will also work.  If you even need it.   Which I so far haven't.<br />
<br />
If the chanter/shaman in the group is afk and I need to slow, I've been getting partial successes with the level 40 slow poison.  Which seems to do okay until they get back.  I don't think we're really meant to be a primary slower.   I also take the dps poison off when slowing.<br />
<br />
I only really solo for xp in the current hot zone Valdeholm.   (With a merc cleric of course).  There I use the dps and slow poisons since agro is no longer an issue.  And it has upped my kill rate there by a lot.  <br />
<br />
I don't know how often the poison would land on higher level mobs.<br />
<br />
I have definitely been giving the all/all dps poison to all my alts.  I even whipped up a couple of stacks of the level 20 stuff for my level 25 pally alt.  At level 25, the pally alt is getting procs for 150.  Which reeealy helps with the dps.<br />
<br />
Enough rambling!<br />
<br />
-Chris</div>
