</div>That would be most excellent.  <img src="images/smilies/emote_smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smile" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
Here is a thought.  We have several utility poisons that I think most rogues would consider highly useful, and several that I suspect they see as somewhat less useful.  Here is how I break it down:<br />
<br />
Useful<br />
<ul><li>Messenger's Bane (snare)</li>
<li>Myrmidon's Sloth (slow)</li>
<li>Quellious' Trauma (hate reduction)</li>
</ul><br />
Less Useful<br />
<ul><li>Fighter's Bane (&quot;clumsy&quot;)</li>
<li>Warlord's Bane (slow and &quot;clumsy&quot;)</li>
<li>Archer's Bane (&quot;accuracy debuff&quot;)</li>
<li>Monk's Bane (&quot;evasion debuff&quot;)</li>
</ul><br />
Why not take a poll to see which of these &quot;Less Useful&quot; poisons rogues would be most willing to give up to get a snare/slow combo poison?  Then you could take the one that is rogues would be willing to give up and just change the effect from whatever it currently is to a some sort of snare/slow combo effect (and perhaps rename the poison if appropriate) while keeping the same recipe.  That might wind up creating the least amount of work for you, while making the EQ rogue community most happy.<br />
<br />
<img src="images/smilies/emote_smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="Smile" class="inlineimg" /><br />
<br />
