    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_478365"><div align="center" style="margin:5px; margin-top:5px; ">
<table width="85%" border="0" align="center" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" bgcolor="#333333" class="bbcodeQUOTE">
  
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3" align="center" valign="middle">
	
	<div align="left"><b><div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"><strong>Ngreth Thergn said:</strong></div></b></div></td>
 
	</tr>
  <tr>   
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/openq.gif" width="30" height="30" ></td>
    <td>
		<div align="left" style="font-size: 12px; color: #999999; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">This is correct.  Internally we call it the &quot;phantom&quot; tick.  the spells will last from 6 to 12 seconds, so on average this lasts 9 seconds.</div>
		</td>
    <td width="30" align="center" valign="middle"><img src="/forums/images/closeq.gif" width="30" height="30" align="right"></td>
  </tr>
</table>
</div>Ngreth I'm generally very happy with the poison revamp, and I think you've been doing a terrific job of working with us to resolve issues and fine tune the various poisons to make them work for us without unbalancing the game.<br />
<br />
However ...<br />
<br />
I would like to say that I am not very happy about the fact that the proc'ed effects from the snare and slow poisons only lasts 6 to 12 seconds.  Let me explain.<br />
<br />
The average number of procs per minute might be 6, but since we are dealing with a random number generator it's highly unlikely that we will be seeing steady, evenly spread procs.  Instead what we often see is a pattern better described by the adjective &quot;streaky&quot; where you might have 3 or 4 procs in rapid succession, and then a period of 30 or more seconds with no procs at all.  Toss in resists and you might commonly see a mob unslowed or unsnared for most of the fight.<br />
<br />
Now unslowed is one thing, but unsnared is another thing entirely, especially if the mob is unsnared at the moment it turns to flee back towards its friends.<br />
<br />
A mob that is unslowed will burn up more of the healer's mana and create a need for more frequent meditation breaks.<br />
<br />
But a mob that is unsnared when it turns to run might &quot;train&quot; the player(s) and cause a wipe.<br />
<br />
With that in mind, would you consider increasing the duration of at least some of these utility effects to something more like 5 to 10 ticks?</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
<br>
