    <div align="left">
	<hr align="left" width="100%" />

    <!-- message -->
    <div align="left" id="post_message_478366">EVerything below is in regards to rogues with max poison skill.<br />
<br />
Taking a look at the effects for Archer's Bane and Monk's Bane I noticed something.<br />
<br />
Archer's Bane X and XI have same proc and effect, a 1% reduction in accuracy.<br />
Types XII and XIII have 2%<br />
Types XIV and XV have 3%<br />
<br />
Monk's Bane is similar with 3% reduction of avoidance, then 6%, then 9% at type XV.<br />
<br />
My question is this:<br />
<br />
2 tiers of poison = same effect. The higher level doesn't add a lowered resist  or any difference at all so why bother?<br />
<br />
That also works in reverse theory. There are those types lower than type X for those poisons, do they use the same effect as type X and XI poisons?  If so then what is the point of making anything higher than the cheapest vendor bought stuff?  Why make a poison FOR your level when it's no different than ones before it.  Specifically, why make level X poison IF type V is the same effect and no resist difference (in regards to the aforementioned poison types). For that matter why not just make type I?<br />
<br />
The debuff types should at least share a similar progression as the dd's do.  I know the myrmidon's sloth does a good progression, why not all of them?<br />
<br />
I can understand the large addition of spell data that would've been added if you did different procs per level.  That work load would've been fairly large but it would've made more sense and been very very nice. However, doing every other tier like you did with the DD's would've been a good compromise.<br />
<br />
To me a higher level (tier) poison should be more potent than the previous ones, even if it's just a matter of a resist rate modifier or alittle dmg, just something has to be better about it.<br />
<br />
But if type X shows the lowest possible effect for that type of poison and there is no difference in resist rate, why bother with making X?  Just make I or II.<br />
<br />
Now for the DD poisons, though they are better with more levels of proc types.  2 tiers =  proc (a) and then next 2 tiers = proc (b) etc... all the way to XIV and then XV has it's own.  What makes them different between the two tiers? Nothing. Same dmg mod for same proc and therefore same resist mod, if any.<br />
<br />
I haven't bothered with making the weird stuff yet, archer and monk bane, I've just been messing with the rogue dd's,  slow, snare and the 2 poisons for others.  The rarity of components + the lack of difference in tiers vs. procs for some of the debuff types just means they'll rarely, if ever, be used.  Specifically the monk and archer bane.<br />
<br />
I would have thought archer bane would've gone all the way to 8% accuracy debuff while monk bane went all the way to the same percentage.  Both going 1% per two tiers and then final boost on type XV.  Since that was what the dd poisons were set up like.<br />
<br />
Bah, I'm rambling, so cutting it here.<br />
<br />
Laters,</div>
    <!-- / message -->
    
    
    <br>
