    <div align="left" id="post_message_478520">Guess I'll have to answer my own question since the focus got put on an aspect in my post that I said was fine.<br />
<br />
Hmm, I'll give it one more shot.<br />
<br />
Archer's Bane<br />
Monk's Bane<br />
<br />
Do they or do they not have the same exact proc from tier 1 through tier X? If they don't have the same exact proc, good cause same proc makes no sense from a potency standpoint.<br />
<br />
IF they do have the same proc then it should be changed imo.  Suggestion for Archer's Bane, tier 1-3 = 1%, tier 4-6= 2%, 7-9= 3%, 10-12= 4%, 13+14= 5%, 15= 6%.  Monk's Bane could go same tier breakup but at 10-12= 5%, 13+14= 7%, then 15 = 9%.<br />
<br />
And of course the rarity of components issue.  Seperate loot table only rogues can see, since we can &quot;acquire&quot; components through our skill.  You'll then be able to &quot;control&quot; the influx better and therefore increase drop rate.  Most bot army farmers don't use a rogue because it's more work than just nuking with mage or wiz for dps.<br />
<br />
I'm happy with the slow poison and dd's and even snare, it's just those particular 2 that make no sense to me.  Stronger poison, more potent poison, more difficult to get components should = BETTER than much lower tier.<br />
<br />
I'm hoping that was more clear than my other post.  I guess this question was a bit vague::<br />
<br />
&quot;The debuff types should at least share a similar progression as the dd's do. I know the myrmidon's sloth does a good progression, why not all of them?&quot;<br />
<br />
I should've specifically stated archer and monk banes and been more concise since that was primarily what my post was about.<br />
<br />
I'm sorry if my stating that I liked the Myrmidon's Sloth progression confused people.<br />
<br />
&quot;I know the myrmidon's sloth does a good progression, why not all of them?&quot;<br />
<br />
The question at the end, I should've been more specific as well and asked, &quot;why not the archer and monk banes?&quot;<br />
<br />
I do hope this post is more focused and easier to understand. It is alittle shorter as well to maybe keep the focus on what I'm asking.<br />
<br />
Laters,</div>
