</div>As no-one else is stepping in I'll try and answer this, because I think it was the same question I had a few weeks ago.<br />
<br />
Examples only (because I don't have the exact info at hand)<br />
Archer's Bane I made with level 20 ingredients will fire procs as though it is level 20<br />
Archer's Bane I made with level 60 ingredients will fire procs as though it is level 60<br />
<br />
Even though it is the same identical spell according to everything you can see on Lucy, the poison made with higher level ingredients will be resisted less on higher level mobs. if you tried to use the level 20 version of Archer's Bane I on a level 60 mob, it would most likely be resisted every time.<br />
<br />
This is the way I interpreted Ngreth's answer.<br />
<br />
The problem is that even the higher level versions of Archer's, Fighter's and Warlord's that I have tested are resisted far too often. They are basically useless. I have the parses for example for level 70 Fighter's against level 70-75 mobs where the proc is resisted 55 times out of 60. The rarity of the ingredients combined with the failure percent in manufacture combined with the resists makes them pointless.</div>
