</div>Your spell was partially successful = 50% mitigation<br />
Your spell was slightly successful = 75% mitigation<br />
<br />
I was hoping to parse the differences between &quot;lowering accuracy&quot; and &quot;mitigated slow&quot; for soloing purposes, but because of the resists I am going to have to find my mala stick or farm some higher level drops.<br />
<br />
There are obvious choices to make when grouping in terms of utility poison (i.e. whether you have a druid or shaman), but to be honest, I would expect to find that the best thing when grouping is DPS and hate reduction more than 90% of the time.<br />
<br />
My current assessment of poisons for soloing, I really did expect better when it came to the utility poisons. There is no &quot;oh wow&quot; factor. None. We are able to solo better than we could before simply because we can do 250+ extra DPS.<br />
<br />
What I would like to see is that the non-standard utility poisons come with massive hate (Fighters, Warlords, Archers) so that they are ONLY useful for soloing. 90% of the time groupers won't care and raiders don't need them. With the massive hate, they will not be overpowered and then the mob resists can be almost eliminated or drastically reduced.</div>
